Definition.WordDefinition: Stressful \Stress"ful\, a. Having much stress. --Rush. [1913 Webster]
stressful adj : extremely irritating to the nerves; "nerve-racking noise"; "the stressful days before a war"; "a trying day at the office" [syn: {nerve-racking}, {nerve-wracking}, {trying}]
